="text-gray-700 italic mb-4">&quot;<!-- -->Our experience with the Virtual Practice platform has been outstanding. As a multidisciplinary team, we find it powerful and intuitive for organizing patient cases, with clear medical records that support precise documentation and effective care.<!-- -->&quot;</p><div><p class="text-gray-700 font-medium">Dr. Georgios Leon - Metabolic Specialist</p><p class="text-gray-600">Precision Medicine Startup, Greece</p></div></div></div><div class="bg-white rounded-lg p-8 shadow-lg"><div class="flex flex-col justify-between h-full"><p class="text-gray-700 italic mb-4">&quot;<!-- -->Allowing doctors to offer telemedicine, remote monitoring health plans, collect payments and the health blog are some of the best features of the Virtual Practice®.<!-- -->&quot;</p><div><p class="text-gray-700 font-medium">Dr. Gerard Saltibus MD</p><p class="text-gray-600">General Practitioner, St. Lucia</p></div></div></div></div></div></section><script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How does the Virtual Practice help providers create and manage lab orders?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Providers can generate lab orders directly from consultation encounters in the Virtual Practice. Each order is stored in the patient's health record and can be easily tracked, managed, and shared with lab partners."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can patients access their lab orders online?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Patients receive lab orders in their Virtual Practice account, accessible through the patient portal or mobile app. They can view, download as PDF, or print the document anytime."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Does the Virtual Practice support lab partner integration?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Absolutely. Clinics can configure one or multiple lab partners within their Virtual Practice. Lab admins can assign orders to the right partner, and results uploaded by the lab automatically update the patient's medical record."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How are lab results shared with patients and providers?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"When a lab partner uploads results against a service request, the files are securely stored in the patient's medical record. Both the patient and provider can access the results through their Virtual Practice interfaces."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who manages lab orders within the clinic?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The Lab Admin role has full oversight. Lab admins get notified whenever a new order is generated, can assign service requests to lab partners, and ensure timely processing."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can the Virtual Practice handle billing for lab orders?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Lab partners can generate bills for lab order fulfilment. Currently, these bills are issued to the clinic (the customer), not directly to the patient."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is the Lab Orders feature powered by AI?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. The Lab Orders feature in the Virtual Practice is not AI-driven. Its value lies in the seamless, secure, and transparent flow of information between providers, patients, and lab partners."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Why should a clinic or healthcare startup use the Virtual Practice for lab orders?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Because it eliminates paperwork, ensures patients never lose access to their orders or results, and integrates lab fulfilment into the broader patient record — making care delivery more connected and efficient."}}]}</script><section class="py-16 bg-gray-50"><div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8"><div class="text-center mb-12"><h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2><div class="w-24 h-1 bg-blue-vibrant mx-auto"></div></div><div class="max-w-4xl mx-au